\s1 An example of fair punishment
\p 
\v 10-11 There was \w a|strong="H3068"\w* man whose mother’s name was Shelomith; she was an Israeli whose father was Dibri from the tribe of Dan. And that man’s father was from Egypt. One day that man and another Israeli man started to fight inside the camp. And while they were fighting, that man cursed \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* [MTY].
